tplinkLagMIB.name: tplinkLagMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tplinkLagMIB.description: Private MIB for system time configuration.

tpLagMaxEntryNum.name: tpLagMaxEntryNum
tpLagMaxEntryNum.description: This object indicates the max number of entries in the lag configuration table.

tpLagLoadBalance.name: tpLagLoadBalance
tpLagLoadBalance.description: This object configures scope of Aggregate Arithmetic, which results in choosing a port to transfer the packets. mac-source-dest: When this option is selected, the Aggregate Arithmetic will apply to the source and destination MAC addresses of the packets. ip-source-dest: When this option is selected, the Aggregate Arithmetic will apply to the source and destination IP addresses of the packets.

tpLagTable.name: tpLagTable
tpLagTable.description: A table that contains informatin about every static lag. LAG (Link Aggregation Group) is to combine a number of ports together to make a single high-bandwidth data path, which can highly extend the bandwidth. The bandwidth of the LAG is the sum of bandwidth of its member port.

tpLagEntry.name: tpLagEntry
tpLagEntry.description: A list of information for every lag.

tpLagIndex.name: tpLagIndex
tpLagIndex.description: This object indicates the index of the lag entry.

tpLagType.name: tpLagType
tpLagType.description: This object indicates the type of the lag entry.

tpLagMember.name: tpLagMember
tpLagMember.description: This object indicates how many ports are included in this lag. The maximum number of ports is eight for 'on' type lag, sixteen for 'active' or 'passive' type lag.

tpLacpSystemPriority.name: tpLacpSystemPriority
tpLacpSystemPriority.description: This object indicates the system priority of the lacp.

tpLacpTable.name: tpLacpTable
tpLacpTable.description: A table that contains the lacp information of every port. LACP (Link Aggregation Control Protocol) is defined in IEEE802.3ad and enables the dynamic link aggregation and disaggregation by exchanging LACP packets with its partner. The switch can dynamically group similarly configured ports into a single logical link, which will highly extend the bandwidth and flexibly balance the load.

tpLacpEntry.name: tpLacpEntry
tpLacpEntry.description: A list of lacp information for every port.

tpLacpPort.name: tpLacpPort
tpLacpPort.description: This object indicates the port number.

tpLacpAdminKey.name: tpLacpAdminKey
tpLacpAdminKey.description: This object indicates the Admin Key of the port. The member ports in a dynamic aggregation group must have the same Admin Key.

tpLacpPortPriority.name: tpLacpPortPriority
tpLacpPortPriority.description: This object indicates the port priority of the port. This value determines the priority of the port to be selected as the dynamic aggregation group member. The port with smaller Port Priority will be considered as the preferred one. If the two port priorities are equal; the port with smaller port number is preferred.

tpLacpMode.name: tpLacpMode
tpLacpMode.description: This object indicates the lacp mode of the port.

tpLacpChan.name: tpLacpChan
tpLacpChan.description: This object indicates the lag number of the port.
